          I am from [New
          Bedford](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Bedford,_Massachusetts),
          MA, a city about 100km south of Boston. I have both US and EU
          citizenship (as a citizen of the Republic of Lithuania).
          
          In 2004, I earned my AB with Honors from the [Department of English
          Language and Literature](http://english.uchicago.edu) at the
          [University of Chicago](http://www.uchicago.edu). The same department
          granted me an AM in 2005. I defended my dissertation “[The Site of
          the Novel](http://moacir.com/academics/dissertation)” in January
          2014, and I received my PhD in June 2014.
          
          From 2009–2012, I lived in Paris as the [ALT
          Fellow](http://alt.uchicago.edu). For 2012–2013, I worked in Vilnius
          to finish my dissertation, under the Blair Dissertation-Year
          Fellowship. Throughout my academic career, I have also worked in many
          different information technology capacities in various departments at
          the University of Chicago.

          From 2014–2015, I was Lecturer in the [Department of Philosophy
          and
          Communications](http://ki.vgtu.lt/faculties/departments/department-of-philosophy-and-political-theory/55100?lang=2)
          at [Vilnius Gediminas Technical
          University](http://www.vgtu.lt/index.php?lang=2). I was also
          appointed in the [Department of Foreign
          Languages](http://ki.vgtu.lt/faculties/departments/department-of-foreign-languages/55098?lang=2).

          I am currently Faculty Fellow in Digital Humanities in the [Department of English](http://english.fas.nyu.edu/page/home) at [New York University](http://www.nyu.edu).
          
          My free time is largely spent engaged as either a consumer of or
          participant in sports and music. I like to kick a ball around and
          play the cavaquinho or my home-made synthesizers.           

          I helped found the [Lithuanian Youth Association of
          France](http://prancuzija.pljs.org) and have served, since
          graduation, as the class secretary of my class at [Phillips
          Academy](http://www.andover.edu).

